         <OBJECT_CONTRACT>
            <TITLE>
               <P>Apache Aviator Integrated Helmets (AAIH)</P>
            </TITLE>
            <REFERENCE_NUMBER>AHCSP/00012</REFERENCE_NUMBER>
            <CPV_MAIN>
               <CPV_CODE CODE="35813000"/>
            </CPV_MAIN>
            <TYPE_CONTRACT CTYPE="WORKS"/>
            <SHORT_DESCR>
               <P>The Apache Capability Sustainment Programme (CSP) team has a requirement to purchase a minimum total of 8 x Apache Aviator Integrated Helmets (AAIH) and 1 x AAIH Alignment Kit as identified as a critical path deliverable for the Apache CSP. It is necessary to seek procurement of the AAIH system direct with the supplier (Elbit Systems of America (ESA) as the Design Authority (DA) and sole vendor of the US Army AAIH system. An AAIH Alignment Kit is required to enable custom fitting of the Helmets to UK pilots.</P>
            </SHORT_DESCR>
            <VAL_TOTAL CURRENCY="GBP">451223</VAL_TOTAL>
            <NO_LOT_DIVISION/>
            <OBJECT_DESCR ITEM="1">
               <CPV_ADDITIONAL>
                  <CPV_CODE CODE="35813000"/>
               </CPV_ADDITIONAL>
               <n2016:NUTS CODE="UKK12"/>
               <MAIN_SITE>
                  <P>Bath and North East Somerset, North Somerset and South Gloucestershire.</P>
               </MAIN_SITE>
               <SHORT_DESCR>
                  <P>The Apache Capability Sustainment Programme (CSP) team has a requirement to purchase a minimum total of 8 x Apache Aviator Integrated Helmets (AAIH) and 1 x AAIH Alignment Kit. It is necessary to seek procurement of the AAIH system direct with the supplier (Elbit Systems of America (ESA) as the Design Authority (DA) and sole vendor of the US Army AAIH system. An AAIH Alignment Kit is required to enable custom fitting of the Helmets to UK pilots. The Authority has set out justifiable grounds for reasons connected with the protection of exclusive rights including for intellectual property rights within this Voluntary Transparency Notice (VTN). The Authority will therefore award this Contract in accordance with Regulation 16(1)((a)(ii) of Defence and Security Public Contracts Regulations (DSPCR) 2011. The DSPCR 2011 implemented the European Union (EU) Directive 2009/81/EC on Defence and Sensitive Security Procurement (from here on referred to as “the directive”) into UK Law.</P>
               </SHORT_DESCR>
               <DIRECTIVE_2009_81_EC>
                  <AC_CRITERIA>
                     <AC_CRITERION>Price</AC_CRITERION>
                     <AC_WEIGHTING>100</AC_WEIGHTING>
                  </AC_CRITERIA>
               </DIRECTIVE_2009_81_EC>
               <NO_OPTIONS/>
               <NO_EU_PROGR_RELATED/>
               <INFO_ADD>
                  <P>An initial cohort of UK Apache pilots will attend US Army delivered D-E conversion training. In order to support the US delivered courses, a procurement of 8 Helmets is required. ESA is a subsidiary of Elbit Systems of America Forth Worth (EFW) and is the only organisation that can qualify the AAIH system on behalf of the US Army.</P>
               </INFO_ADD>
            </OBJECT_DESCR>
         </OBJECT_CONTRACT>
         <PROCEDURE>
            <DIRECTIVE_2009_81_EC>
               <PT_NEGOTIATED_WITHOUT_PUBLICATION>
                  <D_ACCORDANCE_ARTICLE>
                     <D_PROTECT_RIGHTS/>
                  </D_ACCORDANCE_ARTICLE>
                  <D_JUSTIFICATION>
                     <P>The Apache Project Team, part of the UK Ministry of Defence, intends to place a contract with Elbit Systems of America (ESA) to deliver a minimum of 8 x Apache Aviator Integrated Helmets (AAIH) and 1 x AAIH Alignment Kit for the Apache Capability Sustainment Programme. ESA, an EFW subsidiary is the original equipment manufacturer (OEM) and is the only source presently capable and approved by the US Government (USG) to provide these items for the Apache AH-64E system. Intellectual Property Rights that include the helmet system technical design drawings are wholly owned by EFW. The UK needs to maintain a commonality of acceptance standards and build quality with the USG in the provision of the UK AAIH system, failure to maintain commonality may risk product quality and safety standards, potentially resulting in incompatibility with the Apache AH-64E aircraft systems and flight simulators being procured via a Foreign Military Sales (FMS) case (UK-B-WSO) with the USG.</P>
                  </D_JUSTIFICATION>
               </PT_NEGOTIATED_WITHOUT_PUBLICATION>
            </DIRECTIVE_2009_81_EC>
